edu.nd.darts.cimon
Class CoordinateNode

java.lang.Object
  edu.nd.darts.cimon.CoordinateNode
All Implemented Interfaces:
ExpressionNode
public class CoordinateNode
extends Object
implements ExpressionNode

Leaf node of ConditionTree representing an individual condition to monitor. This node will register the condition to be monitored with the metric monitoring agent when active, and will receive trigger events from the monitoring agent to be notified when there is a state change of the condition. This object is similar to ConditionNode, but is used exclusively for geo-coordinate monitoring.

Author:
darts

CoordinateNode(int condition,
               double latitude,
               double longitude,
               int radius,
               ConditionTree tree)
Leaf node of ConditionTree representing an geo-coordinate condition to monitor. This is an object representation of a geo-coordinate condition expression, of the form: [metric] [condition] [threshold]

Parameters:
condition - integer representing condition type of (sub-)expression, as defined in Conditions
latitude - latitude of geo-location condition is based on, 0 for current location
longitude - longitude of geo-location condition is based on, 0 for current location
radius - radius from geo-location, defining threshold
tree - link to ConditionTree this node is a member of

Method Detail

triggered

public boolean triggered(ExpressionNode node)
Description copied from interface: ExpressionNode
Node has been triggered, representing that its state, or one if its child nodes' state, has been set to true. For leaf nodes, the trigger will come from the metric monitoring agent, and the passed value will be null. Trigger may be for a registered anti-condition. Leaf nodes must determine if trigger results in state change to true or false based on current state, since metric monitoring agent is not aware if registered monitor is an anti-condition. For interior nodes, the passed value is the child node that issued the trigger.

Specified by:
triggered in interface ExpressionNode
Parameters:
node - child node whose state changed to true (null if current node is leaf node)
Returns:
true if this trigger causes state of entire ConditionTree to change to true, false otherwise

activate

public void activate()
Description copied from interface: ExpressionNode
Begin actively monitoring the condition or subtree. For leaf nodes, register the condition with the metric monitoring agent. For interior OrNode, activate both child nodes. For interior AndNode, activate one child node. Other child node may be left inactive until first becomes true, using boolean short- circuit analysis to reduce metrics which must be actively monitored at once.

Specified by:
activate in interface ExpressionNode

deactivate

public void deactivate()
Description copied from interface: ExpressionNode
Stop actively monitoring the condition or subtree. For leaf nodes, unregister the condition with the metric monitoring agent. For interior nodes, deactivate child nodes. This allows resource savings by deactivating sub-branches of the tree based on boolean expression short-circuit analysis.

Specified by:
deactivate in interface ExpressionNode
